contents.rsbHtml: The Levenshtein distance is the minimum edit distance between two sequences, counting insertions, deletions, and substitutions each as 1.
contents.rsbText:
'The Levenshtein distance is the minimum edit distance between two
sequences, counting insertions, deletions, and substitutions each as 1.

contents.rsbHtml: Let's see how well Dex handles the conventional dynamic program for this: For each pair of prefixes of the input strings, the Levenshtein distance between those prefixes is the minimum obtainable from the prefixes one shorter by inserting, deleting, or substituting an element.
contents.rsbText:
'Let's see how well Dex handles the conventional dynamic program for
this: For each pair of prefixes of the input strings, the Levenshtein
distance between those prefixes is the minimum obtainable from the
prefixes one shorter by inserting, deleting, or substituting an
element.

contents.rsbHtml: Here is the helper that builds the dynamic program table. Dex's flexible index sets let us encode the fact that the table is 1 larger in each dimension than the inputs. By capturing the relationship statically we avoid both programmer off-by-one errors and runtime array bounds checks.
contents.rsbText:
'Here is the helper that builds the dynamic program table.  Dex's
flexible index sets let us encode the fact that the table is 1 larger
in each dimension than the inputs.  By capturing the relationship
statically we avoid both programmer off-by-one errors and runtime array
bounds checks.

contents.rsbHtml: def levenshtein_table(xs: n=>a, ys: m=>a) -> (Post n => Post m => Nat) given (n|Ix, m|Ix, a|Eq) = yield_state (for _ _. 0) \tab. for i:(Post n). tab!i!first_ix := ordinal i for j:(Post m). tab!first_ix!j := ordinal j for i:n j:m. subst_cost = if xs[i] == ys[j] then 0 else 1 d_subst = get tab!(left_post i)!(left_post j) + subst_cost d_delete = get tab!(left_post i)!(right_post j) + 1 d_insert = get tab!(right_post i)!(left_post j) + 1 tab!(right_post i)!(right_post j) := minimum [d_subst, d_delete, d_insert]
contents.rsbText:
def levenshtein_table(xs: n=>a, ys: m=>a)
    -> (Post n => Post m => Nat) given (n|Ix, m|Ix, a|Eq) =
  yield_state (for _ _. 0) \tab.
    for i:(Post n). tab!i!first_ix := ordinal i
    for j:(Post m). tab!first_ix!j := ordinal j
    for i:n j:m.
      subst_cost = if xs[i] == ys[j] then 0 else 1
      d_subst  = get tab!(left_post  i)!(left_post  j) + subst_cost
      d_delete = get tab!(left_post  i)!(right_post j) + 1
      d_insert = get tab!(right_post i)!(left_post  j) + 1
      tab!(right_post i)!(right_post j) :=
        minimum [d_subst, d_delete, d_insert]

def levenshtein_table(xs: n=>a, ys: m=>a)
    -> (Post n => Post m => Nat) given (n|Ix, m|Ix, a|Eq) =
  yield_state (for _ _. 0) \tab.
    for i:(Post n). tab!i!first_ix := ordinal i
    for j:(Post m). tab!first_ix!j := ordinal j
    for i:n j:m.
      subst_cost = if xs[i] == ys[j] then 0 else 1
      d_subst  = get tab!(left_post  i)!(left_post  j) + subst_cost
      d_delete = get tab!(left_post  i)!(right_post j) + 1
      d_insert = get tab!(right_post i)!(left_post  j) + 1
      tab!(right_post i)!(right_post j) :=
        minimum [d_subst, d_delete, d_insert]

def lines(source:String) -> List String =
  AsList(num_chars, s) = source
  AsList(num_lines, newline_ixs) = cat_maybes for i_char:(Fin num_chars).
    if s[i_char] == '\n'
      then Just(i_char)
      else Nothing
  to_list for i_line:(Fin num_lines).
    start = case prev_ix i_line of
      Just(i) -> right_post newline_ixs[i]
      Nothing -> first_ix
    end = left_post newline_ixs[i_line]
    post_slice(s, start, end)

  n' = size n
  AsList(n', unsafe_cast_table(to=Fin n', xs))

def closest_word(s:String) -> String =
  AsList(_, s') = s
  fst $ minimum_by snd for i.
    AsList(_, word) = words[i]
    (words[i], levenshtein word s')
